VERIFY-5: ABI symbols exported
------------------------------
$ nm -g plugin/cursor/cursor.dylib | grep cliproxy | sort
00000000001a3f60 T _cliproxy_plugin_init
00000000001a3fc0 T _cliproxyPluginCall
00000000001a4030 T _cliproxyPluginFree
00000000001a4080 T _cliproxyPluginShutdown

All four ABI entrypoints are present:
  * _cliproxy_plugin_init    — host bootstrap (stores host API, wires plugin
                                 API vtable, returns ABI version)
  * _cliproxyPluginCall      — main JSON envelope dispatcher; delegates to
                                 plugin/cursor/handlers.go
  * _cliproxyPluginFree      — pairs with C.CBytes for envelope buffers
  * _cliproxyPluginShutdown  — noop cleanup slot

VERIFY-6: ABI-method dry-run (plugin/cursor/handlers_test.go)
-------------------------------------------------------------
Handled methods exercised through dispatch() end-to-end in unit tests:
  * plugin.register            -> capabilities exposed
  * auth.identifier            -> "cursor"
  * auth.parse (cursor JSON)   -> Handled=true, Provider=cursor, Label=email
  * auth.parse (claude JSON)   -> Handled=false (passes to next parser)
  * auth.refresh (passthrough) -> returns same tokens + refreshed timestamp
  * model.static               -> Provider=cursor, non-empty Models
